## <a id='prereqs'></a> Prerequisites

Solace PubSub+ for Pivotal Platform requires the following:

* Pivotal Platform version 2.1.x. or later.
* Java buildpack v4.x.x or later.
* MySQL database, which can be made available in one of these methods:
  * Internal deployment as part of the Solace PubSub+ for Pivotal Platform on a management VM
     * [Internal MySQL](#required_mysql_internal)
     * [Internal MySQL (Highly Available)](#required_mysql_internal_ha)
  * As service from a deployment of [MySQL for Pivotal Platform](http://docs.pivotal.io/p-mysql/index.html). Please ensure to configure for a High Availability setup and with service plans offering a minimum of 100&nbsp;MB. See [MySQL for Pivotal Platform](#required_mysql_for_pcf).
  * External when MySQL is already deployed outside Pivotal Platform, it may be offered as a user provided service instance to Solace PubSub+ for Pivotal Platform, see [External MySQL](#required_mysql_external).
* If using TCP Routes: [TCP Routes Requirements](#tcp_routes_requirements)


## <a id='install'></a> Install Solace PubSub+ for Pivotal Platform

To install Solace PubSub+ for Pivotal Platform, do the following:

1. Download the product file from the [Solace Downloads page](https://products.solace.com/download/PUBSUB_Pivotal Platform_STAND)

1. Upload the product file on the Ops Manager **Installation Dashboard**.

1. Click **Add** next to the uploaded Solace PubSub+ tile in the Ops Manager **Available Products** view to add it to your staging area.

1. Click the **Solace PubSub+** tile.

1. Follow the steps in the section below to configure the tile.


